    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1977-03-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1977-03-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="29"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d29">
                <head>29. Memorandum From the Director of the United States Information Agency
                        (<persName corresp="#p_RJE_1">Reinhardt</persName>) to all <gloss
                        target="#t_USIA_1">USIA</gloss> Employees<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d29fn1">Source: National Archives, <gloss target="#t_RG_1"
                            >RG</gloss> 306, <gloss target="#t_USIA_1">USIA</gloss> Historical
                        Collection, Office of the Director, Biographic Files Relating to <gloss
                            target="#t_USIA_1">USIA</gloss> Directors and Other Senior Officials,
                        1953–2000, Entry A–1 1069, Box 23, <persName corresp="#p_RJE_1">John E.
                            Reinhardt</persName>, Speeches, 1977–1978. No classification
                        marking.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1977-03-25">March 25, 1977</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <salute>TO MY <gloss target="#t_USIA_1">USIA</gloss> COLLEAGUES</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>It is with a great sense of humility, honor and dedication that I accept
                    President <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1">Carter</persName>’s nomination<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d29fn2">See <ref target="#d21fn2">footnote 2, Document
                        21</ref>.</note> and now assume the position of Director of the U.S.
                    Information Agency.</p>
                <p>During the months ahead, as we discuss and determine the future course of <gloss
                        target="#t_USIA_1">USIA</gloss>, I shall count on your support. I come to my
                    new position with a knowledge and understanding of the importance of our work
                    and of the professionalism which characterizes our career service. Each of us is
                    convinced that public diplomacy is an integral part of the foreign policy
                    process and that its practitioners must be dedicated, imaginative, and
                    untiring.</p>
                <p>It is an honor for me to join with you once again and to have the opportunity to
                    participate in the further development and refinement of our programs.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RJE_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">John E. Reinhardt</hi>
                        </persName>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Director</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
